{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8695a298-1277-4d66-8e4c-0fc8b0f9ada5","content":"Here's how to migrate:\n\n**1. Update packages** in your test `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\nKeep your existing `xunit` (2.9.3) package reference.\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `dotnet test` works with MTP starting in .NET SDK 9+. For older SDKs, you may need `--enable-microsoft-testing-platform` or run the executable directly.\n- If you use `RunSettings` or VSTest-specific filters, review the [MTP filter syntax](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform-overview) as it differs slightly.\n- Remove any other VSTest adapters you no longer need.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fc2da1cb-695d-4608-b1db-9002ba0cc1e2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":374,"requestId":"5C3C:F5EE8:7BEE1:9C4E0:69F549F0"},"id":"5327e64d-b34c-4b8b-9127-e2f0b4f7e55f","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:48:56.802Z","parentId":"00f0a7d3-2f5d-4812-aac4-497dda15a3a7"}
